      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI is less than 5% between medium and fine mesh solutions, confirming mesh-independent results at Level 2.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the FDA generic pump geometry (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 5.8M cells, fine: 14.2M cells). GCI for the scalar stress-based hemolysis index was 3.2% between medium and fine meshes. Medium mesh selected for production runs, providing adequate accuracy within acceptable computational cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) are documented and match CFD boundary conditions within ±5% for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "FDA interlaboratory study experimental conditions are fully documented. CFD boundary conditions replicate measured inlet flow rates (2–8 L/min), impeller speeds (2000–3500 RPM), and blood analogue viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s). Maximum deviation between nominal and applied boundary conditions is 2.1%, within acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index values fall within one standard deviation of the mean experimental values across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against FDA interlaboratory experimental data at all five flow-speed operating points. All predictions fall within ±1 SD of experimental mean. Mean absolute error across operating points is 0.18 mg/dL, consistent with inter-laboratory variability in the reference dataset."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The CFD QoI (scalar stress-based hemolysis index) is directly linked to the clinical endpoint (red blood cell damage) and the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is computed directly from CFD-predicted scalar shear stress fields integrated along particle pathlines. This QoI is the same metric used in the regulatory submission and maps directly to the clinical outcome of blood trauma. The power-law hemolysis model coefficients (Giersiepen et al.) are consistent with those accepted in prior 510(k) submissions for centrifugal pumps."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties are sufficiently similar to the COU device and conditions to support extrapolation of validation conclusions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump, which is a canonical geometry representative of the CPB device class. Operating conditions span the full clinical range of interest. Blood analogue fluid properties match those used in the device submission. Geometric differences between validation and COU geometries are within the tolerance ranges under investigation, supporting direct applicability of validation conclusions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, formal iterative convergence monitoring to residual tolerance of 1e-5 is sufficient; detailed solver error quantification not required.",
      "rationale": "MRL 2 does not require explicit numerical solver error quantification beyond standard convergence monitoring. Residuals for all transport equations converged to 1e-6 for all simulations. Not assessed as a separate factor per MRL 2 scoping guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, documented simulation plan and independent review of setup parameters is sufficient to address use error without formal quantification.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second qualified CFD engineer prior to production runs. Boundary condition inputs, material property assignments, and solver settings documented in the simulation plan. Formal use-error quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, selection of SST k-omega turbulence model and power-law hemolysis model is justified by literature precedent; formal model-form uncertainty quantification not required.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on established literature precedent for rotating blood-contacting devices. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen 1990 coefficients) is the regulatory standard for this device class. Model-form uncertainty not formally quantified per MRL 2 scoping; literature-based justification is sufficient."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, nominal input values with documented sources are sufficient; formal input uncertainty propagation not required.",
      "rationale": "All model input parameters (geometry dimensions, fluid viscosity, density, rotational speed, flow rates) specified at nominal values with documented sources. Sensitivity of hemolysis index to input variations addressed qualitatively through the five-point operating envelope study. Formal uncertainty propagation not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
